<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-12-07T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-07T19:00:00-05:00" n="132" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d132">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 Pacific War/695:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Norweb</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-07T19:00:00-05:00">December 7, 1941—7
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 7:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>656. The Minister for Foreign Affairs<note n="61a" xml:id="d132fn1">Alfredo Solf y Muro.</note> just requested me to transmit the
                                following message for President Roosevelt from President Prado:
                                    <quote rend="blockquote">
                                    <p>President Prado desires to make known to the United States
                                        and especially to President Roosevelt that the attitude of
                                        Peru is one of entire cooperation in giving to the United
                                        States any assistance or support in measures which it may be
                                        necessary to take to meet the situation in the Pacific.</p>
                                </quote></p>
                            <p>I hope that I may have a telegraphic acknowledgement of this
                                message.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Norweb</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>